article.headline: Texas State 27, McNeese State 17
article.story: LAKE CHARLES, La. (AP) -- Bradley George threw three touchdowns to lead Texas State to a 27-17 win over McNeese State Saturday. Texas State (2-4, 1-1 Southland Conference) took advantage of McNeese turnovers, and George used backup Chase Wasson as the go-to receiver to give the Bobcats a 17-3 halftime lead. Wasson caught two TD passes in the first quarter, one a 12-yarder with 9:55 left in the quarter and a 10-yard pass with 1:16 left. McNeese (2-4, 0-1) scored on a 25-yard field goal in the first quarter, and tried to mount a comeback in the second half. The Cowboys scored on a 30-yard pass from Derrick Fourroux to Quinten Lawrence with 4:30 left in the third quarter and on a fourth quarter 4-yard Fourroux pass to Wesley Mangan with 9:27 left in the game. But Texas State kept pace, scoring on a 20-yard pass from George to Morris Crosby with 5:52 remaining in the third quarter and on a 34-yard field goal with 12:53 left in the game. George connected on 12-of-23 passes for 201 yards. Crosby finished with three catches for 79 yards and Jamie Leonard had 72 rushing yards on nine carries. For the Cowboys, Fourroux completed 16-of-27 passes for 186 yards, but allowed three interceptions. Carlese Franklin added 95 yards on seven runs and Leonard ended with 72 yards on nine catches.
